<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="375" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Type material</emphasis>
: 
<materialsCitation collectingDate="2022-01-01" collectingDateMax="2022-12-31" collectingDateMin="2022-01-01" country="United Kingdom" county="For" location="The" municipality="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" specimenCount="three" specimenCount-male="2" stateProvince="Surrey" typeStatus="syntypes">
Only 
<specimenCount type="male">three males</specimenCount>
are preserved in the Kirby collection (NHML). These males are probably 
<typeStatus>syntypes</typeStatus>
, even if the original description only mentions the female (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, RCL" journalOrPublisher="The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="36 - 39" refId="B44" refString="Perkins, RCL, 1918. The synonymy of Andrena wilkella K., and its allies, with notes on habits, as confirming specific distinctions. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 54: 36 - 39" title="The synonymy of Andrena wilkella K., and its allies, with notes on habits, as confirming specific distinctions." volume="54" year="1918">Perkins 1918</bibRefCitation>
and note above, under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Praz &amp; Genoud &amp; Vaucher &amp; Bénon &amp; Monks &amp; Wood" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Fabaceae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena afzeliella" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afzeliella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Andrena afzeliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Both 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. ovatula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="ovatula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. ovatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Stoeckhert, E" editor="Schmiedeknecht, O" journalOrPublisher="Gustav Fischer, Jena" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="897 - 986" refId="B64" refString="Stoeckhert, E, 1930. Andrena Fabr. In: Schmiedeknecht, O, Ed., Die Hymenopteren Nord- und Mitteleuropas. Gustav Fischer, Jena: 897 - 986" title="Andrena Fabr." volumeTitle="Die Hymenopteren Nord- und Mitteleuropas." year="1930">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stöckhert">Stoeckhert</normalizedToken>
(1930)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. afzeliella" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="afzeliella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. afzeliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in the 
<collectingCountry name="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</collectingCountry>
near the type locality of 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. ovatula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="ovatula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. ovatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of Andrena ovatula (blue dots) and A. afzeliella (red dots)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.82761.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707505" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">7</figureCitation>
). We are not confident in the identification of these 
<specimenCount type="male">three males</specimenCount>
(see above under 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. afzeliella" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="afzeliella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. afzeliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<collectingCounty>For</collectingCounty>
this reason, we submitted a request to the 
